KANO – Nigeria Customs Kano/Jigawa area office has announced the seizure of unwholesome foods item and drugs worth over N1.9 billion. Muhammad Umar, Area Controller, Kano/Jigawa Area Command told Reporters in Kano that the seizure has been handed over to NDLEA for action. Umar said that 1593 bags of foreign rice with a street value of N46,078m was seized, adding that 34,940 sachets of tramadol with a street value put at N1.890m was also confiscated. -Advertisement- He further disclosed that 535 pieces of Cikabrin of 20 grams were also seized within the last three months and handed over to the relevant authority. The Controller revealed that 1237 foreign soap with street value at N3,171m was seized by the area office, stressing that 131 bales of second hands clothes valued at N9, 825m were taken out circulations. Umar however warned, “smugglers to desist from Act of smuggling or they will soon meet their Waterloo.” He, therefore, called on genuine businessmen to explore the potentials of Inland Containers, Dala Dry Port, and Kano Free Trade Zones.